Product name: Mens Weekender Bag, Travel Bag for Men, Canvas Weekender, Mens Travel Bag
Description:
I put a lot of time working on this weekender bag, but it worth it 1000%. I made it for two main purposes: when I go to gym and when I make short trips over the weekend by plane or by car. There's nothing I would add to make it better. It's perfect. It really is. Light, large enough for as many clothes as you need, but it will still fit as a  cabin luggage, very well structured, with a bottom made of thick leather. On the sides, the two pockets will carry your phone, the wallet or the keys, a book, a map, a kindle, your glasses and a small bottle of water.
This bag is also made of waxed canvas, because there's nothing worst then getting at the hotel with your clothes wet. 
The shades it gets over time make the waxed canvas a special fabric. And because of that, the saddle leather is the high class partner it deserves to have.
Both the waxed canvas and the saddle leather evolve and get better over time. Every scratch is recorded and the marks and the shades will remind you of all the journeys you took, to discover the world and to discover yourself. I see these two materials like a photographic film that captures the present for the future.
To preserve the character of the fabrics and to make them last longer, I waterproofed the leather and the lining. Together with the waxed canvas, they make an amazing weekender bag, ready for a long walk on a rainy day.
The height is aprox. 33 cm/ 13'', the deep is aprox. 28 cm/ 11" and the length is aprox. 55 cm/ 21.5".

I am not a jeweler nor a gemologist but love vintage and estate jewelry. The information I impart is usually given to me when I acquire each individual piece. Therefore, sometimes I have quite a lot of details and other times very few. I try very hard to be as accurate as possible yet ALL descriptions and/or measurements are approximate. I test all gemstones on a Presidium Gem Tester and it is quite accurate. It cannot determine however whether the actual gemstone is a natural gemstone or a man made gemstone as they both are identical in every way. An accredited Gemologist would be the only individual qualified to do so. Stones such as turquoise, opals etc. do not register on the Presidium.

Product name: Antique Daguerreotype Photo Antique Photograph Tintype Ambrotype Cabinet Card CDV Sixth Plate Full Leather Case Civil War Cabinet Photo
Description:
~Description~ 
Frenchman Louis Daguerre invented the daguerreotype in Paris nearly 180 years ago and marked the beginning of photography as we know it. After it's invention in 1839 the daguerreotype became wildly popular. At the height of its popularity in 1853 there were reportedly 86 studios in New York City alone. 
Their mirror like reflection makes identification easy and each component can help with dating. First a brass cover was placed over the image, which in this case takes what they called a nonpareil shape. This piece was called the "mat" and it commonly featured elaborate designs like this in the early 1850's. Initially, a glass sheet would be placed atop the mat and the set would be fixed inside a case but starting in 1847 studios began adding an additional brass cover known as the preserver. This preserver features elaborate designs which again is a trait commonly seen starting in the early 1850's. The case is made of wood and adorned with leather to provide quality protection and presentation. Cases of this type were used exclusively into the mid 1850's until thermoplastic union cases hit the market. 
~Measurements~ 
Length: 3 Inches
Width: .75 Inches
Height: 3.5 Inches 
~Condition~
This piece is in excellent antique condition with very minimal wear. The pictures remain very clear and the other components are undamaged. The case is in great condition with both of the clasps fully functional and the binding still in tact. 
~Section~
Antique photographs are a favorite of ours and if you are as interested in these treasures as we are don't forget to check out the splendid range or daguerreotypes, ambrotypes, and tintypes featured here in the shop.

Commentary:
For How-to-Measure:
Bust
▲This is not your bra size
▲Wear a no padded bra(your dress will have a built-in bra)
▲Relax arms at sides
▲Pull tape across the fullest part of the bust
Waist
▲Find the natural waist
▲This is the smallest part of the waist
▲Usually about 1 in. above belly button
▲Keep tape slightly loose to allow for breathing room
Hips
▲Find the widest part of the hips
▲Usually about 7 in. below natural waist
▲Tape should brush across both hipbones
Hollow to Floor
▲Stand straight with feet together 
▲Measure in BARE FEET
▲Begin at the hollow space between the collarbones and pull tape straight down to the floor
▲To fit high heels, I’ll add an extra 5 cm onto custom-sized floor-length dresses and dresses with trains.(If you have special requirement, like you'll wear 10 cm heels, please let me know.)

Description:
Simple and easy style.  This sterling silver cartilage hoop is made with sterling silver wire in your choice of gauge and size.  Choose 20g for septum rings and nose hoops, or maybe a delicate tragus ring with 22g wire.  We offer 10mm, 8mm and 6mm hoop sizes for perfect fit for all your piercing needs.  All our Class X hoops are crafted in our Pacific Northwest studio using quality materials and with thought for your comfort.  
****This listing is for a single hoop.
   Size check.<<< 
The outer edge of the 8mm is the size of Home Button on the iPhone. 10mm is slightly larger.  6mm slightly smaller.  
-Hoop sizes are based on wire gauge and interior diameters.
Interior diameter size options:
6mm - very tiny and may be OK for a tiny ear that is pierced close to the edge. Possible sites include daith, tragus and rook.
8mm - slightly larger and fits more people. Possible sites include nostril, helix, daith, tragus, and second lobe.
10mm - good for a piercing farther away from the edge of the ear. Possible sites include lobe, helix, septum.
These are only estimations.  Class X wants you to be happy with your purchase.  Every piercing is different so be sure to take notice of your own for proper fit as we can not offer returns due to hygienic reasons. 
-Wire gauge options are;
20 gauge - Standard 
22 gauge - Slim wire (delicate)
Item Information:
All of our cartilage and nose hoops are a seamless style,  twist open and close, and can be worn on any piercing.
They are made with sterling silver wire, which contains 92.5% silver and 7.5% copper (925.)  
Hoop Care - 
To extend the life of your hoops, please remove before bathing, swimming and sleeping.
Store in a dry, clean ziplock bag.
Sterling silver will tarnish over time.  To clean your hoops, add mild dishsoap to a bowl of warm water and let soak for a few minutes.  Gently use a soft cloth to remove any impurities, rinse and buff dry.

Product name: Carry On Luggage, Overnight Bag, Cabin Luggage, Carry On Bag, Cabin Bag, Overnight Luggage
Description:
I put a lot of time making this Carry On Luggage, but it worth it 1000%. I made it for two main purposes: when I go to gym and when I make short trips over the weekend by plane or by car. There's nothing I would add to make it better. It's perfect. It really is. Light, large enough for as many clothes as you need, but it will still fit as a  cabin luggage, very well structured, with a bottom made of thick leather. On the sides, the two pockets will carry your phone, the wallet or the keys, a book, a map, a kindle, your glasses and a small bottle of water.
This bag is also made of waxed canvas, because there's nothing worst then getting at the hotel with your clothes wet. 
The shades it gets over time make the waxed canvas a special fabric. And because of that, the saddle leather is the high class partner it deserves to have.
Both the waxed canvas and the saddle leather evolve and get better over time. Every scratch is recorded and the marks and the shades will remind you of all the journeys you took, to discover the world and to discover yourself. I see these two materials like a photographic film that captures the present for the future.
To preserve the character of the fabrics and to make them last longer, I waterproofed the leather and the lining. Together with the waxed canvas, they make an amazing weekender bag, ready for a long walk on a rainy day.
The height is aprox. 33 cm/ 13'', the deep is aprox. 28 cm/ 11" and the length is aprox. 55 cm/ 21.5".
